pon reality. Will Smith's character relies upon rather dubious techniques to win big gains. In real life, those "Cons" place a lot more of the risk upon the played, rather than the player. Even at the very end, at the climax of the final scam, the entire Con depends upon a shot from a handgun being placed between the 3rd and the 4th rib, or something like that. Margot Robbie turns in another stellar performance in this film, not long after "The Wolf of Wall Street". It was nice to see Gerald McRaney, in true "Major Dad" form, back in action as well. All in all, the film was fun to watch, but had a manufactured and unbelievable plot.Always keep focus. *** May contain strong spoilers *** I like Will Smith. He has such a good laugh and presence. "Focus" is a piece of a professional entertainment playing in the step below the big league. The piece starts off with recognizable topics and characters, just to spin off in another direction... or is it? The research of the criminals, the characters, the personalities and the psychological issues behind the story is solid. Could have been even more; as it is it is good enough. One character in the movie is a big foreigner that comes with the most hysterical "I am honest and straight forward just to confuse you"- type of guy. Great! The question that comes through the screen and lands in the knee of the observer is as follows; who is who, and who is really who...?  Summary: A good story with twists and roll-overs. A while, there were too much of a regular "rip-off criminal movie". Will Smith is good, so are the other actors. Farhad; laughs! 6,8 out of 10Charming Con Artists If there is one thing that this dark comedy thriller Focus delivered to its viewers,it is the presence of its charming lead stars in Will Smith and Margot Robbie.Without these stars,the film would have fallen flat especially on the latter part wherein the story was unbearable especially when the Will Smith character Nicky "Mellow" Spurgeon simply into a bad guy who use anyone for his con acts. The film starts when Jess Barrett decides to go under internship and eventually the wing of Nicky to learn more about the tricks of the trade in con acts and many other criminal activities.They go together at first in New Orleans wherein they start to con many people during the Superbowl. As Jess becomes great as a con artist,she and Nicky develop a romantic relationship.But after the Superbowl,Nicky decides to leave Jess as romance cannot be a part of being a con man.After three years,they meet again at Buenos Aires. They renew their relationship and later found themselves involved in a con that includes billionaire motor sport team owner which could eventually endanger their lives. The first act at New Orleans was good enough.But the it fall somewhat flat in the second act in Buenos Aires.Too bad that the film basically had to mainly rely on the charms of Smith and Robbie to become bearable. Sad but true.Also,it had the twists and turns of the story especially when both Nicky and Jess were captured was far from intriguing as it basically consisted of clich√©s seen in many movies before.Surprisingly good Surprisingly good! Excellent profanity, and good supporting cast. Hot chick, too. Farhad does a good turn as best friend and partner. He is adept and highly watchable.  And where can I binge watch PanAm? I guess that is where they got their starlet. A good reader and very easy to look at. I am going to go back with a microscope for every frame with her in it. Central casting, fersher, but man, does she hit all the marks! She has the right mix of Audrey Hepburn, Melissa McCarthy, and Charlise Theron. Somebody is going to make a lot of money with her.Its alright but again, its not the best I loved Will Smith and Margot Robbie teaming up together for the first time and Im excited to see them again in the film "Suicide Squad". I thought the storyline with this was too fast and really not getting to the point of being a conman. Its 